WESTERN CAP - Cape Town police are on a manhunt after discovering drugs worth R4,7-million in Mitchells Plain. Police raided a house in West Gate on Sunday. They searched the premises and discovered 106,000 mandrax tablets. The narcotics were hidden in an abandoned vehicle. READ: Man bust with mandrax worth R3 million It's believed the house was being used as a distribution point. Police expect to make arrests soon. eNCA